settings.name: logic_rules
settings.description: What placement logic is to be used to generate the world.

settings.name: logic_no_night_tokens_without_suns_song
settings.description: Nighttime Skulltulas will logically require Sun's Song.

settings.name: open_forest
settings.description: Set the state of Kokiri Forest and the path to the Deku Tree.

settings.name: open_kakariko
settings.description: Set the state of the Kakariko Village gate.

settings.name: open_door_of_time
settings.description: Open the Door of Time by default, without the Song of Time.

settings.name: zora_fountain
settings.description: Set the state of King Zora, blocking the way to Zora's Fountain.

settings.name: gerudo_fortress
settings.description: Set the requirements to access Gerudo Fortress.

settings.name: bridge
settings.description: Set the requirements for Rainbow Bridge.

settings.name: trials
settings.description: Set the number of required trials in Ganon's Castle.

settings.name: starting_age
settings.description: Set the age Link will start as.

settings.name: shuffle_interior_entrances
settings.description: Shuffles interior entrances. "Simple" shuffles houses and Great Fairies; "Full" includes Windmill, Link's House, Temple of Time, and Kak potion shop.

settings.name: shuffle_grotto_entrances
settings.description: Shuffles grotto and grave entrances.

settings.name: shuffle_dungeon_entrances
settings.description: Shuffles dungeon entrances. Opens Deku, Fire and BotW to both ages. "All" includes Ganon's Castle.

settings.name: shuffle_overworld_entrances
settings.description: Shuffles overworld loading zones.

settings.name: owl_drops
settings.description: Randomizes owl drops from Lake Hylia or Death Mountain Trail as child.

settings.name: warp_songs
settings.description: Randomizes warp song destinations.

settings.name: spawn_positions
settings.description: Randomizes the starting position on loading a save. Consistent between savewarps.

settings.name: shuffle_bosses
settings.description: Shuffles boss entrances.

settings.name: triforce_hunt
settings.description: Gather pieces of the Triforce scattered across the world to complete the game.

settings.name: triforce_goal
settings.description: The number of Triforce pieces required to complete the goal.

settings.name: extra_triforce_percentage
settings.description: The percentage of the Triforce piece goal to add to the multiworld pool as extras. With high numbers, you may need to randomize additional locations to have enough items.

settings.name: bombchus_in_logic
settings.description: Bombchus are properly considered in logic. The first pack has 20 Bombchus, Kokiri Shop and Bazaar sell refills, and getting them opens up bowling minigame.

settings.name: dungeon_shortcuts
settings.description: Shortcuts to dungeon bosses are available without any requirements.

values.name: choice
values.description: Must define dungeon_shortcuts_list manually in YAML.

settings.name: mq_dungeons_mode
settings.description: Choose between vanilla and Master Quest dungeon layouts.

values.name: specific
values.description: Must define mq_dungeons_list manually in YAML.

settings.name: mq_dungeons_count
settings.description: Number of MQ dungeons, chosen randomly.

settings.name: bridge_stones
settings.description: Set the number of Spiritual Stones required for the Rainbow Bridge.

settings.name: bridge_medallions
settings.description: Set the number of medallions required for the Rainbow Bridge.

settings.name: bridge_rewards
settings.description: Set the number of dungeon rewards required for the Rainbow Bridge.

settings.name: bridge_tokens
settings.description: Set the number of Gold Skulltula Tokens required for the Rainbow Bridge.

settings.name: bridge_hearts
settings.description: Set the number of hearts required for the rainbow bridge.

settings.name: shuffle_mapcompass
settings.description: Determine where maps and compasses will be located.

values.name: keysanity
values.description: add them to the multiworld pool

settings.name: shuffle_smallkeys
settings.description: Determine where small keys will be located.

values.name: keysanity
values.description: add them to the multiworld pool

settings.name: shuffle_hideoutkeys
settings.description: Control where to shuffle the Thieves' Hideout small keys.

values.name: keysanity
values.description: add them to the multiworld pool

settings.name: shuffle_bosskeys
settings.description: Deterine where boss keys will be located, excluding Ganon's Castle.

values.name: keysanity
values.description: add them to the multiworld pool

settings.name: enhance_map_compass
settings.description: If enabled, the map will identify whether a dungeon is vanilla or Master Quest, and the compass will reveal the dungeon reward.

settings.name: shuffle_ganon_bosskey
settings.description: Determine where the boss key for Ganon's Castle will be located.

values.name: keysanity
values.description: add it to the multiworld pool

settings.name: ganon_bosskey_medallions
settings.description: Set how many medallions are required to receive Ganon Boss Key.

settings.name: ganon_bosskey_stones
settings.description: Set how many stones are required to receive Ganon Boss Key.

settings.name: ganon_bosskey_rewards
settings.description: Set how many rewards are required to receive Ganon Boss Key.

settings.name: ganon_bosskey_tokens
settings.description: Set how many tokens are required to receive Ganon Boss Key.

settings.name: ganon_bosskey_hearts
settings.description: Set how many hearts are required to receive Ganon Boss Key.

settings.name: key_rings
settings.description: Dungeons have all small keys found at once, rather than individually.

values.name: choose
values.description: Must define key_rings_list manually in YAML.

settings.name: shuffle_song_items
settings.description: Set where songs can appear.

settings.name: shopsanity
settings.description: Randomize shop contents.

values.name: fixed_number
values.readableName: User-defined number of shuffled items per shop (configure below)

values.name: random_number
values.readableName: Random number of shuffled items per shop

settings.name: shop_slots
settings.description: Number of items per shop to be shuffled into the multiworld pool.

settings.name: shopsanity_prices
settings.description: Controls prices of shop items.

values.name: starting_wallet
values.description: Must max out this wallet to purchase.

values.name: adults_wallet
values.description: Must max out this wallet to purchase.

values.name: giants_wallet
values.description: Must max out this wallet to purchase.

values.name: tycoons_wallet
values.description: Must max out this wallet to purchase.

settings.name: tokensanity
settings.description: Shuffle token rewards from Gold Skulltulas into the multiworld pool.

settings.name: shuffle_scrubs
settings.description: Shuffle items sold by Business Scrubs, and set the prices.

settings.name: shuffle_child_trade
settings.description: Controls the behavior of the start of the child trade quest.

settings.name: shuffle_freestanding_items
settings.description: Shuffles freestanding rupees, recovery hearts, Shadow Temple Spinning Pots, and Goron Pot.

settings.name: shuffle_pots
settings.description: Shuffles pots and flying pots which normally contain an item.

settings.name: shuffle_crates
settings.description: Shuffles large and small crates containing an item.

settings.name: shuffle_cows
settings.description: Cows give items when Epona's Song is played.

settings.name: shuffle_beehives
settings.description: Beehives drop an item when destroyed by an explosion, the Hookshot, or the Boomerang.

settings.name: shuffle_kokiri_sword
settings.description: Whether the Kokiri Sword is shuffled into the pool.

settings.name: shuffle_ocarinas
settings.description: Whether the Fairy Ocarina and Ocarina of Time are shuffled into the pool.

settings.name: shuffle_gerudo_card
settings.description: Whether the Gerudo Membership Card is shuffled into the pool.

settings.name: shuffle_beans
settings.description: Whether the Bean Salesman's bean pack is shuffled into the pool. The Bean Salesman will sell a random item from the pool for 60rs.

settings.name: shuffle_medigoron_carpet_salesman
settings.description: Shuffle the items sold by Medigoron and the Carpet Salesman at Hanted Wasteland.

settings.name: shuffle_frog_song_rupees
settings.description: Shuffles the purple rupees received from the Zora's River frogs.

settings.name: no_escape_sequence
settings.description: Skip the tower collapse sequence between the fights with Ganondorf and Ganon.

settings.name: no_guard_stealth
settings.description: The crawlspace into Hyrule Castle skips to Zelda.

settings.name: no_epona_race
settings.description: Epona can always be summoned with Epona's Song.

settings.name: skip_some_minigame_phases
settings.description: Dampe Race and Horeseback Archery give both rewards if the second condition is met on the first try.

settings.name: complete_mask_quest
settings.description: All masks are immediately available to borrow from the Happy Mask Shop.

settings.name: useful_cutscenes
settings.description: Reenables the Poe cutscene in Forest Temple, Darunia in Fire Temple, and Twinrova introduction. Mostly useful for glitched.

settings.name: fast_chests
settings.description: All chest animations are short. If disabled, big items will have the long animation to them.

settings.name: free_scarecrow
settings.description: Pulling out the Ocarina while near a scarecrow spot summons Pierre without playing the song.

settings.name: fast_bunny_hood
settings.description: Bunny Hood lets you move 1.5× faster, like in Majora's Mask.

settings.name: plant_beans
settings.description: Pre-plants all 10 Magic Beans in the soft soil spots.

settings.name: chicken_count
settings.description: How many Cucco Anju wants for an item in the past.

settings.name: big_poe_count
settings.description: Number of Big Poes required for the Poe Collector's item.

settings.name: fae_torch_count
settings.description: Number of lit torches required to open Shadow Temple.

settings.name: correct_chest_appearances
settings.description: Changes chest textures and/or sizes to match their contents.

values.name: classic
values.default: This is the old behavior of CSMC.

settings.name: minor_items_as_major_chest
settings.description: Hylian Shield, Deku Shield, and Bombchus appear in big/gold chests.

settings.name: invisible_chests
settings.description: Chests visible only with Lens of Truth. Logic is not changed.

settings.name: correct_potcrate_appearances
settings.description: Unchecked pots and crates have a different texture; unchecked beehives will wiggle.

values.name: textures_content
values.description: Pots and crates have an appearance based on their contents.

values.name: textures_unchecked
values.description: All unchecked pots/crates have the same appearance.

settings.name: hints
settings.description: Gossip Stones can give hints about item locations.

settings.name: misc_hints
settings.description: Controls whether the Temple of Time altar gives dungeon prize info and whether Ganondorf hints the Light Arrows.

settings.name: hint_dist
settings.description: Choose the hint distribution to use. Affects the frequency of strong hints, which items are always hinted, etc.

settings.name: text_shuffle
settings.description: Randomize text in the game for the lulz.

settings.name: damage_multiplier
settings.description: The amount of damage taken by Link.

settings.name: deadly_bonks
settings.description: Bonking on a wall or object will hurt Link.

settings.name: no_collectible_hearts
settings.description: Enemies and objects will not drop heart refills.

settings.name: starting_tod
settings.description: What time of day the game starts on.

settings.name: blue_fire_arrows
settings.description: Ice arrows can melt red ice and break the mud walls in Dodongo's Cavern.

settings.name: fix_broken_drops
settings.description: Fixes two broken vanilla drops: Deku Shield in child Spirit Temple, and Magic Drop on GTG Eye Statue.

settings.name: start_with_consumables
settings.description: Start with a full complement of Deku Sticks and Nuts.

settings.name: start_with_rupees
settings.description: Start with a full rupee wallet. New wallets will also be full of rupees.

settings.name: item_pool_value
settings.description: Changes the number of items available in the game.

settings.name: junk_ice_traps
settings.description: Add ice traps to the item pool.

settings.name: ice_trap_appearance
settings.description: Changes the appearance of ice traps as freestanding items.

settings.name: default_targeting
settings.description: Preselects the default targeting option.

settings.name: display_dpad
settings.description: Show D-pad icon on HUD for quick actions (Ocarina, Hover Boots, Iron Boots).

settings.name: dpad_dungeon_menu
settings.description: Show separated menus on the pause screen for dungeon keys, rewards, and Vanilla/MQ info.

settings.name: correct_model_colors
settings.description: Make in-game models match their HUD element colors.

settings.name: background_music
settings.description: Randomize or disable background music. If you are streaming and turning this off to play your own music, please be mindful of licensing.

settings.name: fanfares
settings.description: Randomize or disable item fanfares.

settings.name: ocarina_fanfares
settings.description: Enable Ocarina songs as fanfares. These are longer than usual fanfares.
